<para>
  The <classname>SquareBrush</classname> is used when selecting pixels
  with the <link
  linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Graphics_n.Toolbox.Pixel_Select.Brush"><classname>Brush</classname></link>
  selection tool in the <link
  linkend="Section-Graphics-PixelSelection">Pixel Selection</link>
  toolbox. All pixels within a square centered on the mouse are
  selected as the mouse moves over the image.  The edge of the square
  is twice<footnote>
  <para>
    So that a square brush with <code>size=R</code> is about the same
    size as a <link linkend="RegisteredClass-GfxCircleBrush">circular
    brush</link> with <code>radius=R</code>.
  </para>
  </footnote> the given <varname>size</varname> parameter, which is given
  in  <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Microstructure-Coordinates"><emphasis>physical</emphasis></link>
  units.

</para>
<figure id="Figure-SquareBrush">
  <title>Selection with a Square Brush</title>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
	  <imagedata fileref="FIGURES/pixelselect/squarebrush.png"
                 contentwidth="648px" format="PNG"/>
    </imageobject>
    <caption>
	  <simpara>
	    (a) A selection being made with the square brush, with
	    <code>size=8</code>.  The physical size of the
	    &micro; is 92&times;91.
      </simpara>
      <simpara>
        (b) The selection made in (a).  Compare with the circular brush in
	    <xref linkend="Figure-CircleBrush"/>.
	  </simpara>
    </caption>
  </mediaobject>
</figure>


  

